Package: WFC
Title: Workflow-Oriented Survey Weight Calibration
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Kunxiang", family = "Ma", email = "mkx07080412@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("WEIAN DATA TECH (Beijing) Co., Ltd.", role = c("cph", "fnd")))
Author: Kunxiang Ma [aut, cre], WEIAN DATA TECH (Beijing) Co., Ltd. [cph, fnd]
Maintainer: Kunxiang Ma <mkx07080412@gmail.com>
Description: Provides a disciplined precheck, execution, and diagnostics workflow
    for survey weighting and raking with schema-agnostic dimensions and canonical
    target objects, including an auditable guided workflow and bilingual
    human-facing reports. Converts calibrated and replicate weights into standard
    survey designs, provides optional broom-style result projections, and records
    serializable production pipeline provenance. Supports soft calibration with
    auditable margin relaxation and entropy balancing for exact moment matching,
    plus panel attrition weighting, high-influence unit diagnostics, Fay's
    balanced repeated replication, and opt-in parallel execution for long runs.
